[{"id":"VR625283","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block of mass m attached to the right end of a compressed spring on a flat surface. There are 3 positions indicated from left to right on the surface, labeled x equals negative A, x equals 0, and x equals positive A. The block is currently held at position x equals negative A. The flat surface is at a height of h above the ground.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR625283.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is attached to a horizontal spring, as shown, and is free to move on a horizontal surface at a height <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>h</mi></math></span></span> above the ground. Friction between the block and the surface is negligible. The block is initially held at rest at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals negative A\"><math alttext=\"x equals negative A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>âˆ’</mo><mi>A</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> with the spring compressed. The block is released, and it moves to the right, passing position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 0\"><math alttext=\"x equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>, at which point the spring is at its unstretched length, with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. The block then momentarily comes to rest at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals positive A\"><math alttext=\"x equals positive A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>A</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following is a correct expression for the total mechanical energy of the system consisting of only the spring and the block after the block is released?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR625283_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus one half k A squared, plus m g h\"><math alttext=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus one half k A squared, plus m g h\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus one half k A squared\"><math alttext=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus one half k A squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus m g h\"><math alttext=\"one half m v sub 0, end sub, squared plus m g h\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>h</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half k A squared\"><math alttext=\"one half k A squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]